<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Caesar Cipher</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/caesar_style.css">
</head>
<body>
	<p id="description">
		This is a simple Caesar cipher application.<br>
		Write a word, phrase or a sentence.<br>
		Then, choose a number for the factor<br>
		by which you want to apply the cipher.
	<p>
	<form>
		<label>Text: </label>
		<input type="text" name="phrase" size="30"><br>
		<label>Factor:</label>
		<input type="number" step="1" name="factor" id="factor"><br>
		<br>
		<input type="submit" value="Encipher" class="button">
	</form>
	<% if output %>
	<p>
		<h3>The enciphered text is</h3>
		<%= output %>
	</p>
	<% end %>
	<div id="wiki">
		If you don't know what the Caesar cipher is or want to know more, visit the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caesar_cipher">wikipedia article</a>.<br>
		<a href="/" id="back" class="button">Back to index</a>
	</div>
</body>
</html>